The third branch (
Figs. 3
F, G: TB; 
Table 1
) is a broad–based triangular, thin, much flattened medio–dorsal outgrowth. This outgrowth is folded once or several times over itself; when it is stretched, it can be seen that the margins are rather undulate and that the outgrowth tapers to the apex where there is a small spine.
